The paper proposes a method for learning feature nonlinearities using non-convex regularized linear regression, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The method is applicable to various applications, including those involving image processing (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the selection of a sparse subset of good features, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistics (cs.ST). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST, and cs.CV.
